01:12:17,039 --> 01:12:19,305
- How are you?
- I'm good, man. How you doing?

1179
01:12:19,477 --> 01:12:20,740
So is Sophie here?

1180
01:12:20,913 --> 01:12:23,509
You know what?
I haven't seen her. Yeah.

1181
01:12:23,685 --> 01:12:25,052
- Chris?
- Who?

1182
01:12:25,222 --> 01:12:27,454
- You know, my manager.
- I'm sorry. Have fun.

1183
01:12:27,626 --> 01:12:30,757
- Yeah.
- Hey, Michelle. Good to see you, babe.

1184
01:12:30,933 --> 01:12:31,924
Hey, how's it going?

1185
01:12:36,878 --> 01:12:38,745
Hey, Ray, what's up, man?

1186
01:12:39,282 --> 01:12:40,912
How's it going?

1187
01:13:06,404 --> 01:13:07,394
Hey.

1188
01:13:07,573 --> 01:13:08,905
- Where's Sophie?
- Hang on.

1189
01:13:09,510 --> 01:13:13,177
Hang on. God, she's here. Please
don't let her through. Don't let her through.

1190
01:13:13,351 --> 01:13:16,117
We cannot let her talk to Cora.
She's gonna ruin everything.

1191
01:13:16,291 --> 01:13:18,021
- Who?
- Sophie. She hates the song.

1192
01:13:18,194 --> 01:13:20,688
- She hates the song you wrote?
- Yes. She hates it.

1193
01:13:20,866 --> 01:13:24,066
But she wrote the song.
Why does she hate it?

1194
01:13:24,239 --> 01:13:26,676
We had a little disagreement.

1195
01:13:26,845 --> 01:13:28,439
Hi there, Soph, how are you?

1196
01:13:28,615 --> 01:13:30,847
- Hey, Sophie.
- Good evening.

1197
01:13:31,019 --> 01:13:33,855
So you brought something,
did you, Sophie?

1198
01:13:34,025 --> 01:13:36,826
Yes. My mother told me,
"Never go to a party empty-handed"...

1199
01:13:36,998 --> 01:13:41,462
...so I went to the Zen Eatery and got
a selection of cookies. No, thank you.

1200
01:13:41,640 --> 01:13:43,304
Nirvana Nougat.

1201
01:13:48,087 --> 01:13:50,251
Hey. It's my favorite writers.

1202
01:13:50,424 --> 01:13:51,757
Hi, C. How are you?

1203
01:13:51,928 --> 01:13:53,921
We brought you some cookies,
from all of us.

1204
01:13:54,500 --> 01:13:56,766
Thank you. Derek.

1205
01:13:56,938 --> 01:13:58,703
Cora, I really wanted to talk to you...

1206
01:13:58,875 --> 01:14:01,346
About the fact that
we're gonna have to leave early...

1207
01:14:01,514 --> 01:14:04,178
...to finish this song
which has become important to us...

1208
01:14:04,353 --> 01:14:06,345
...in both an artistic and spiritual sense.

1209
01:14:06,524 --> 01:14:08,756
You can't leave yet. Come see the house.

1210
01:14:08,929 --> 01:14:12,060
I wanna show you the roof. It's upstairs.

1211
01:14:12,235 --> 01:14:14,432
Do you know...? Well...

1212
01:14:17,179 --> 01:14:21,620
Cora, I definitely see how much
you've thought about the song and...

1213
01:14:21,788 --> 01:14:25,124
Great roof. In a very interesting place
as well, right at the top...

1214
01:14:25,295 --> 01:14:28,756
- Sophie was about to say something.
- Was she? I don't think she was. No.

1215
01:14:28,935 --> 01:14:31,964
She looks like she's about
to say something, then just... clams up.

1216
01:14:32,142 --> 01:14:36,549
What I wanted to say is that I appreciate
that you're bringing thought to the music...

1217
01:14:36,718 --> 01:14:40,556
...but I really and honestly feel
that we're pandering.

1218
01:14:42,930 --> 01:14:46,665
Which means trying to make others like you,
which I think is a really nice thing.

1219
01:14:46,838 --> 01:14:49,537
I do a lot of it.
"Just going out pandering, be back soon."

1220
01:14:49,710 --> 01:14:54,117
The song is about the struggle, you know,
to show your true feelings.

1221
01:14:54,285 --> 01:14:57,223
And your very confident sexual display...

1222
01:14:57,392 --> 01:15:01,390
...is, you know, a total contradiction
of the fear and insecurity.

1223
01:15:01,567 --> 01:15:04,733
No, I don't think so.
And my fans really love it when I dance.

1224
01:15:04,907 --> 01:15:07,207
- You're a wonderful dancer.
- That's a fair point.

1225
01:15:07,379 --> 01:15:10,749
- My last CD only went to number two.
- But in this case, if you trust us...

1226
01:15:10,919 --> 01:15:14,551
And Shakira is breathing down my neck.
So I wanna dance.

1227
01:15:16,597 --> 01:15:18,863
You shall dance.

1228
01:15:19,503 --> 01:15:23,806
But thank you for your honesty, Sophie.
Cherish your passion.

1229
01:15:23,978 --> 01:15:27,850
- Well, thank you.
- Cora, Timberlake's here. Wants to say hi.

1230
01:15:28,120 --> 01:15:29,919
Nice to see you, C. Talk to you later.

1231
01:15:30,091 --> 01:15:32,358
And I'm looking forward
to the new last verse.

1232
01:15:32,528 --> 01:15:33,724
- Cora, wait.
- It's over.

1233
01:15:33,898 --> 01:15:36,494
It was a very nice try,
but you have hit the karmic wall.

1234
01:15:36,671 --> 01:15:40,736
With no help from you.
You just stood there. Talk about pandering.

1235
01:15:40,912 --> 01:15:43,577
I did not pander. I just told her
what she wanted to hear.

1236
01:15:43,752 --> 01:15:46,154
- I'm gonna go tell her the truth.
- You just did.

1237
01:15:46,323 --> 01:15:48,920
Are you gonna use flash cards this time?
You're stubborn.

1238
01:15:49,095 --> 01:15:52,067
And you're not stubborn enough
to stand up for what's good.

1239
01:15:52,235 --> 01:15:55,470
I mean, I just don't wanna see you
do what you did on your solo album.

1240
01:15:55,642 --> 01:15:56,974
Yes, yes, yes.

1241
01:15:58,448 --> 01:16:00,918
I bought it. The last copy.

1242
01:16:01,821 --> 01:16:04,418
All right, well, I insist
on paying you back immediately.

1243
01:16:04,593 --> 01:16:06,027
9.99, right? Do you have a penny?

1244
01:16:06,196 --> 01:16:08,860
You were trying so hard to get a hit
that it wasrt you.

1245
01:16:09,035 --> 01:16:11,130
The songs were soulless.

1246
01:16:11,307 --> 01:16:13,937
I agree. But ours has soul, so...

1247
01:16:14,112 --> 01:16:17,449
But not if we ruin it. And you know that.
Why are you so scared to care?

1248
01:16:17,618 --> 01:16:19,714
Because it won't matter.

1249
01:16:19,890 --> 01:16:23,795
Because behind
all her Buddhism-in-a-thong philosophy...

1250
01:16:23,965 --> 01:16:27,233
...what she cares about
is seats filled and units sold.

1251
01:16:27,405 --> 01:16:29,068
Nothing's gonna make her your pal...

1252
01:16:29,243 --> 01:16:31,543
...any more than years with Colin
made him mine.

1253
01:16:31,714 --> 01:16:34,150
Because in the end, it's all just business.

1254
01:16:34,319 --> 01:16:36,221
- What is?
- All of it. Everything.

1255
01:16:36,389 --> 01:16:38,360
That's why they call it
the music business.

1256
01:16:38,528 --> 01:16:41,295
It's a good thing.
I wish everything in life was that clear.

1257
01:16:41,467 --> 01:16:43,937
I want something from you,
you want something from me.

1258
01:16:44,105 --> 01:16:45,630
No false promises or expectations.

1259
01:16:49,249 --> 01:16:50,717
Well.

1260
01:16:50,885 --> 01:16:53,118
Congratulations on your feel-good song.

1261
01:16:55,962 --> 01:16:57,487
Can I get you a drink?

1262
01:17:25,020 --> 01:17:27,992
There's plenty of time.
We have the night, part of the morning...

1263
01:17:28,160 --> 01:17:30,062
...teeniest little bit of the afternoon.

1264
01:17:59,623 --> 01:18:02,116
I can't read it.
What does that...? What does that say?

1265
01:18:02,862 --> 01:18:04,765
"Sorry, I can't do this."

1266
01:18:09,877 --> 01:18:13,817
Sorry, I can't do this

1267
01:18:15,354 --> 01:18:18,793
Not sure about the scansion.
What...? What, are you leaving?

1268
01:18:18,961 --> 01:18:23,163
Yeah. I'm sorry.
Maybe I'll think of something later.

1269
01:18:23,336 --> 01:18:26,001
There is no later.
She needs the song tomorrow.

1270
01:18:26,176 --> 01:18:29,114
If we don't give it to her,
she's gonna go to someone else.

1271
01:18:29,282 --> 01:18:30,648
I will have lost the job.

1272
01:18:30,818 --> 01:18:32,947
I'm sorry.

1273
01:18:33,757 --> 01:18:36,490
- Okay, look.
- No, I want to help. I do.

1274
01:18:36,663 --> 01:18:38,963
I wanna help you finish, but I can't.

1275
01:18:39,135 --> 01:18:43,439
I can't write when I feel like this.
I'm not inspired.

1276
01:18:43,610 --> 01:18:47,983
I don't care. I don't care if you're inspired.
Inspiratiors for amateurs.

1277
01:18:48,153 --> 01:18:51,648
I just want four lines. Please.
I just want four lines.

1278
01:18:51,826 --> 01:18:54,696
- I can't.
- Oh, but you can and you won't.

1279
01:18:54,866 --> 01:18:58,237
- Are you saying I wanted this to happen?
- I'm saying that's what you do.

1280
01:18:58,406 --> 01:19:00,740
You push and push
and move the furniture around...

1281
01:19:00,912 --> 01:19:02,609
...and talk all the time...

1282
01:19:02,781 --> 01:19:05,218
...and screw everything up
just like he said.

1283
01:19:05,688 --> 01:19:08,352
Who's he? What are you talking about?
What are you saying?

1284
01:19:08,528 --> 01:19:11,294
I read the book because I wanted
to come to you and say:

1285
01:19:11,467 --> 01:19:15,201
"You're not at all like Sally Michaels."
But actually, he's got you spot on.

1286
01:19:15,374 --> 01:19:18,939
- What are you saying?
- I'm saying Sloan Cates was right.

1287
01:19:20,017 --> 01:19:24,013
Oh, my God. Please take that back.

1288
01:19:24,192 --> 01:19:27,653
The poor, innocent, helpless
"'I can't write,' she says to herself" girl...

1289
01:19:27,831 --> 01:19:29,858
...has co-authored
three-quarters of a hit...

1290
01:19:30,036 --> 01:19:33,167
...and is holding it ransom
because she can't get what she wants.

1291
01:19:33,343 --> 01:19:36,804
You think life is this fairy tale.

1292
01:19:36,984 --> 01:19:40,616
When it turns out that everything
doesn't end happily, you can't deal with it.

1293
01:20:01,900 --> 01:20:07,207
Mama says I can't, Daddy says I can
But now my body just wants to slam

1294
01:20:08,480 --> 01:20:10,005
Slam

1295
01:20:10,985 --> 01:20:14,355
- C, Alex Fletcher is here.
- Hey, Alex.

1296
01:20:14,826 --> 01:20:18,059
C, could I...? Could I have a quick word?
Thanks a lot.

1297
01:20:18,433 --> 01:20:20,836
- Derek, how are you? Good to see you.
- Alex Fletcher.

1298
01:20:23,878 --> 01:20:25,973
Yo, so how's my girl Sophie, man?

1299
01:20:26,149 --> 01:20:28,779
Yeah, no, she's keeping it pretty real.

1300
01:20:28,954 --> 01:20:30,650
Yeah, what a girl.

1301
01:20:30,824 --> 01:20:34,890
C, hi. Listen, it's about
the new last verse.

1302
01:20:35,067 --> 01:20:38,130
It's not completely formed
in the classical sense yet.

1303
01:20:38,306 --> 01:20:41,768
It's more a kind of string of words
that you can connect in almost any way.

1304
01:20:41,946 --> 01:20:44,213
- I think it's quite innovative.
- I got the lyrics.

1305
01:20:44,385 --> 01:20:48,119
Sophie faxed them over this morning.
They are so beautiful.

1306
01:20:48,292 --> 01:20:50,559
It's what I always wanted to say
to my boyfriend.

1307
01:20:50,732 --> 01:20:53,567
It's the perfect end to the song.

1308
01:20:53,938 --> 01:20:58,572
There are moments
When I don't know if it's real

1309
01:20:58,747 --> 01:21:03,587
Or if anybody feels the way I feel

1310
01:21:03,757 --> 01:21:06,820
I need inspiration

1311
01:21:07,598 --> 01:21:13,338
Not just another negotiation

1312
01:21:14,980 --> 01:21:20,321
All I wanna do
Is find a way back into...

1313
01:21:21,492 --> 01:21:24,054
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, yeah. Sorry, sorry.

1314
01:21:24,230 --> 01:21:27,327
I just... I just completely,
I don't know, spaced out.

1315
01:21:27,504 --> 01:21:30,236
That's okay. Let's take it from the top
with the new intro.

1316
01:21:30,410 --> 01:21:32,209
Yep. Great.

1317
01:21:34,117 --> 01:21:38,218
Yeah, Cora Corman and Alex Fletcher

1318
01:21:38,393 --> 01:21:40,386
Way back into love

1319
01:21:46,041 --> 01:21:47,032
Hi.

1320
01:21:47,679 --> 01:21:49,238
Hello.

1321
01:21:49,950 --> 01:21:53,856
I bought these for your children because
one should never show up empty-handed.

1322
01:21:54,425 --> 01:21:58,798
They're aliens.
Clearly, I have no children. Here.

1323
01:21:58,968 --> 01:22:01,768
- Here, let me get that for you.
- Thank you.

1324
01:22:04,912 --> 01:22:08,408
I am gonna go to the office.

1325
01:22:09,021 --> 01:22:11,788
- I am too. Have fun with those.
- Bye.

1326
01:22:18,105 --> 01:22:20,372
Put them there, thanks.

1327
01:22:22,414 --> 01:22:24,144
You coming to the concert tomorrow?

1328
01:22:24,585 --> 01:22:26,646
Can't disappoint Lucy.

1329
01:22:26,823 --> 01:22:29,020
Yes, yes, very important.

1330
01:22:29,930 --> 01:22:34,598
Chris is bringing his daughter as well,
so should be fun.

1331
01:22:34,939 --> 01:22:37,877
I just wanted to say
I thought your last verse was fantastic.

1332
01:22:38,313 --> 01:22:39,302
Thank you, Alex.

1333
01:22:40,283 --> 01:22:42,617
And I'm very sorry about what I said.

1334
01:22:42,788 --> 01:22:46,421
Well, you know, life isn't a fairy tale
and I have to grow up...

1335
01:22:46,596 --> 01:22:48,462
...and I'm gonna do that in Florida.

1336
01:22:49,133 --> 01:22:51,104
Well, that's just ridiculous.

1337
01:22:51,271 --> 01:22:54,540
No one grows up in Florida.
Unless they're an orange.

1338
01:22:54,712 --> 01:22:57,512
Well, I'm managing
the new Weight-Not branch in Boca Raton.

1339
01:22:57,684 --> 01:23:00,348
You should be writing,
not fighting cellulite.

1340
01:23:00,523 --> 01:23:03,086
Well, I can do both.
We need a new marketing campaign.

1341
01:23:03,261 --> 01:23:05,027
Swimsuit season is coming up.

1342
01:23:06,602 --> 01:23:08,196
Thing is...

1343
01:23:09,608 --> 01:23:11,703
...I can't...

1344
01:23:15,285 --> 01:23:17,586
...compose without you.

1345
01:23:17,758 --> 01:23:20,628
Thanks, but I don't think
it's a good idea.

1346
01:23:25,507 --> 01:23:27,373
All right. You're obviously very busy.

1347
01:23:32,822 --> 01:23:34,415
Good luck.

1348
01:23:35,260 --> 01:23:36,557
You too.

1349
01:25:23,943 --> 01:25:25,606
Cora!

1350
01:25:30,089 --> 01:25:32,821
- Gracie, aren't you excited?
- Let's go.

1351
01:25:34,531 --> 01:25:38,528
You know what? You guys, just go.
I think I'm gonna skip it.

1352
01:25:38,706 --> 01:25:41,176
- No, come on. You can't skip it.
- You know what, kids?

1353
01:25:41,345 --> 01:25:43,815
I'm gonna talk to your aunt, okay?
Gary, take them in.

1354
01:25:43,983 --> 01:25:46,010
- Should I meet you...?
- Do it. How hard is it?

1355
01:25:46,187 --> 01:25:47,679
- Go, walk, sit.
- Find your seats.

1356
01:25:47,857 --> 01:25:50,795
Honey, I need a second. Thank you.
Love you. You're a good man.

1357
01:25:50,964 --> 01:25:52,159
Now, listen to me.

1358
01:25:52,333 --> 01:25:56,900
Those kids have told all of their friends
that their aunt wrote Cora's new hit song.

1359
01:25:57,077 --> 01:25:59,673
And they wanna share this with you.
You gotta go in.

1360
01:25:59,848 --> 01:26:02,786
Yeah. No, I know. I know. I just...

1361
01:26:02,954 --> 01:26:06,688
I don't know how I'm gonna go in there
and look at him.

1362
01:26:07,897 --> 01:26:11,097
I know. It's just one night, though,
and I really think you need this.

1363
01:26:11,270 --> 01:26:15,802
And then he'll go his way
and you'll go yours. Okay?

1364
01:26:20,423 --> 01:26:22,655
Do you have her autograph?

1365
01:26:22,827 --> 01:26:24,091
- Isn't this exciting?
- Yeah.

1366
01:26:24,697 --> 01:26:25,723
This is so cool.

1367
01:26:26,535 --> 01:26:29,405
- Yeah, weirdo. This is so cool.
- It's great.

1368
01:26:29,574 --> 01:26:31,908
We're in the Cora fan club.
Can we? Please, Mom?

1369
01:26:32,079 --> 01:26:34,778
- Okay.
- Cora!

1370
01:26:56,662 --> 01:26:58,597
Cora!

1371
01:26:58,766 --> 01:26:59,995
Cora!

1372
01:27:10,555 --> 01:27:12,219
Cora!

1373
01:27:36,841 --> 01:27:40,076
- Look, there she is!
- Is that Cora?

1374
01:27:56,615 --> 01:27:58,015
I'm starting to believe, boy

1375
01:27:59,186 --> 01:28:00,620
That this was meant to be, boy

1376
01:28:00,789 --> 01:28:03,455
'Cause I believe in karma

1377
01:28:03,628 --> 01:28:06,099
Boy, do you believe in karma?

1378
01:28:08,973 --> 01:28:12,935
Each time you put your lips to mine
It's like a taste of Buddha's delight

