1400
01:29:46,167 --> 01:29:49,799
...written by Mr. Alex Fletcher.

1401
01:29:49,974 --> 01:29:50,964
Wait.

1402
01:29:56,988 --> 01:30:00,119
What? Alex Fletcher and my sister.

1403
01:30:00,295 --> 01:30:01,695
How quickly they forget.

1404
01:30:02,900 --> 01:30:05,736
Let's just go and come back
when the song's over. You and me.

1405
01:30:08,010 --> 01:30:09,842
- Actually, I'm gonna go.
- No. What?

1406
01:30:10,013 --> 01:30:12,041
- Yeah, no. I'm fine. Just...
- Are you sure?

1407
01:30:12,219 --> 01:30:15,454
Yeah, I'm fine. I just wanna be alone.
Just take care of the kids.

1408
01:30:36,568 --> 01:30:39,300
It's never been easy for me

1409
01:30:41,110 --> 01:30:44,845
To find words to go along with a melody

1410
01:30:47,990 --> 01:30:52,363
But this time there's actually
Something on my mind

1411
01:30:54,403 --> 01:30:59,004
So please forgive
These few brief awkward lines

1412
01:31:01,182 --> 01:31:05,180
Since I met you
My whole life has changed

1413
01:31:07,596 --> 01:31:12,129
It's not just my furniture
You've rearranged

1414
01:31:14,309 --> 01:31:20,014
I was living in the past
But somehow you've brought me back

1415
01:31:20,521 --> 01:31:26,021
And I haven't felt like this
Since before Frankie said, "Relax"

1416
01:31:26,200 --> 01:31:28,693
And though I know

1417
01:31:28,871 --> 01:31:31,843
Based on my track record

1418
01:31:32,011 --> 01:31:35,006
I might not seem like the safest bet

1419
01:31:38,457 --> 01:31:40,723
All I'm asking you

1420
01:31:41,296 --> 01:31:45,202
Is don't write me off just yet

1421
01:31:56,727 --> 01:32:00,725
For years I've been telling myself
The same old story

1422
01:32:02,940 --> 01:32:07,506
That I'm happy to live off
My so-called former glories

1423
01:32:09,386 --> 01:32:15,331
But you've given me a reason
To take another chance

1424
01:32:15,833 --> 01:32:21,299
Now I need you despite the fact
That you've killed all my plants

1425
01:32:21,644 --> 01:32:23,704
And though I know

1426
01:32:23,881 --> 01:32:26,911
I've already blown more chances

1427
01:32:27,088 --> 01:32:30,117
Than anyone should ever get

1428
01:32:34,034 --> 01:32:36,528
All I'm asking you

1429
01:32:36,708 --> 01:32:40,477
Is don't write me off just yet

1430
01:32:43,754 --> 01:32:48,321
Don't write me off just yet

1431
01:33:05,932 --> 01:33:07,561
Alex!

1432
01:33:29,613 --> 01:33:32,175
- Nobody backstage.
- I have to get up there. I know Cora.

1433
01:33:32,352 --> 01:33:35,152
- I don't care what you want.
- I know Cora. I wrote this song.

1434
01:33:35,324 --> 01:33:36,314
She's okay.

1435
01:33:36,493 --> 01:33:38,929
- There's nobody backstage.
- I said she's okay, right?

1436
01:33:39,099 --> 01:33:41,091
- Well, you vouch for her, then.
- Thank you.

1437
01:33:41,270 --> 01:33:42,363
What's wrong with you?

1438
01:33:42,538 --> 01:33:45,066
As soon as Cora's done "Slam,"
we'll need you on-stage.

1439
01:33:45,244 --> 01:33:47,680
Okay, got it. Got it.
Thanks very much. Cheers.

1440
01:33:49,318 --> 01:33:51,346
Slam

1441
01:33:51,958 --> 01:33:57,367
Mama says I can't, Daddy says I can
But now my body just wants to slam

1442
01:33:58,671 --> 01:33:59,832
Slam

1443
01:34:01,777 --> 01:34:03,644
Come to a concert, don't bring anything?

1444
01:34:04,716 --> 01:34:07,312
Alex, that song.

1445
01:34:07,487 --> 01:34:10,756
Yeah, I know. I'm sorry.
It's the best I could do. You could fix it.

1446
01:34:10,928 --> 01:34:14,025
No. That song was dinner.

1447
01:34:17,508 --> 01:34:19,774
Mama says I can't, Daddy says I can

1448
01:34:23,286 --> 01:34:24,414
Thank you!

1449
01:34:27,963 --> 01:34:31,026
I want you to hear my new single.

1450
01:34:31,870 --> 01:34:33,601
Thank you!

1451
01:34:33,774 --> 01:34:38,546
"Way Back Into Love," music and lyrics
by Sophie Fisher and Alex Fletcher.

1452
01:34:38,717 --> 01:34:41,187
What happened to steamy and sticky?

1453
01:34:41,356 --> 01:34:44,385
I explained to Cora that it violated
the very core of the lyric...

1454
01:34:44,562 --> 01:34:46,428
...and corrupted the purity of the song.

1455
01:34:46,599 --> 01:34:49,537
When that didn't work, I told her
it would help me win you back.

1456
01:34:49,706 --> 01:34:50,969
And that did it.

1457
01:34:51,143 --> 01:34:55,480
Turns out that although she thought
the Dalai Lama was, incredibly, a llama...

1458
01:34:55,651 --> 01:34:57,848
...she is, in fact, quite the romantic.

1459
01:34:58,589 --> 01:35:00,492
- Go. Go. Go.
- Okay, Mr. Fletcher.

1460
01:35:00,661 --> 01:35:02,129
Thank you.

1461
01:35:02,297 --> 01:35:07,501
Trapped in the past
I just can't seem to move on

1462
01:35:07,675 --> 01:35:12,208
I've been hiding all my hopes
And dreams away

1463
01:35:12,385 --> 01:35:17,190
Just in case I ever need 'em
Again someday

1464
01:35:17,360 --> 01:35:20,355
I've been setting aside time

1465
01:35:21,369 --> 01:35:26,505
To clear a little space
In the corners of my mind

1466
01:35:27,515 --> 01:35:33,517
All I wanna do
Is find a way back into love

1467
01:35:37,201 --> 01:35:44,170
I can't make it through
Without a way back into love

1468
01:35:50,861 --> 01:35:55,359
I've been watching
But the stars refuse to shine

1469
01:35:55,537 --> 01:36:00,378
I've been searching
But I just don't see the signs

1470
01:36:00,548 --> 01:36:04,283
I know that it's out there

1471
01:36:04,454 --> 01:36:09,727
There's gotta be something
For my soul somewhere

1472
01:36:09,899 --> 01:36:14,101
I've been looking for someone
To shed some light

1473
01:36:14,274 --> 01:36:18,579
Not somebody just to get me
Through the night

1474
01:36:18,951 --> 01:36:21,980
I could use some direction

1475
01:36:23,794 --> 01:36:27,894
And I'm open to your suggestions

1476
01:36:28,770 --> 01:36:35,443
All I wanna do
Is find a way back into love

1477
01:36:38,155 --> 01:36:44,692
I can't make it through
Without a way back into love

1478
01:36:45,804 --> 01:36:50,177
And if I open my heart to you

1479
01:36:50,346 --> 01:36:54,754
I'm hoping you'll show me what to do

1480
01:36:54,922 --> 01:36:59,090
And if you help me to start again

1481
01:37:00,199 --> 01:37:07,113
You know that I'll be there
For you in the end

1482
01:40:09,222 --> 01:40:18,231
THE END
